When a limit is exceeded the API returns a 429 Too Many Requests and includes rate‑limit headers (X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset).

Typical responses:
- Per‑minute rate limit: 429 with an error like
  { "error": { "code": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED", "message": "Rate limit exceeded. Try again in 60 seconds" } }
- Monthly query limit: 429 with a body like
  {
    "success": false,
    "error": "Monthly query limit exceeded",
    "usage": {
      "current": 101,
      "max": 100,
      "exceeded": true,
      "reset_at": "2026-02-01T00:00:00Z"
    }
  }

(You may also see an INSufficient_CREDITS error format for query/credit failures in some responses.)

